FBIS3-44468 "drchi002_n_94012" FBIS-CHI-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 Economic & Agricultural 1,600 Kilometers of New Railways Built in 1993 HK3112105093 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0821 GMT 31 Dec 93 HK3112105093 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, December 31 (CNS) -- This year has seen the biggest ever investment in railway construction and the greatest length of new railways in China's history, according to the Ministry of Railways. By the end of November, 53 medium- and large-scale rail construction projects saw investment of RMB [renminbi] 16.06 billion, three times as much as for the same period last year. Work done for these projects included 150 million cubic metres of road-bed, 88,000 metres of tunnels, 160,000 metres of medium- and large-scale bridges and some 1,655.2 kilometres of track-laying. The initial stage of the Beijing-Kowloon railway has proceeded smoothly with 1,360 kilometres of the roadbed being laid by the end of November, 84 percent of the total length while 532 kilometres of track, one-third the total length, has been laid. The second-phase project of the Daqin railway and the double- track project of the Zhejiang-Jiangxi railway have passed inspection while electrification of the Zhangxia section of the Yingtan-Xiamen railway has also been completed.
